06/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu announced Sunday (5 January) that National Intelligence Service Deputy Director Petrit Myftari has been relieved of his duties. 
The move was at the request of Prime Minister Fatos Nano, who proposed replacing Myftari with Ylli Alushi. 
No word yet on the reason for the shake-up.
Also Sunday, Albania's Foreign Ministry officially condemned the murders of Tahir Zemaj and his two sons in Kosovo on Saturday. 
The ministry called it a "criminal act that threatens security and the image of Kosovo." (ATA - 05/01/03)
